 Aimee ee rssersavive Fyre 7\nIPORAIMAD os os xu eanns tpn tos arssscsist strane IB rae\nTITLE INSURANCE STOCKS,\nEr Es SPAR Me FIR 90 10\nNPRAABION anes susmnnsmnsnsrmss sae nsk cto SE\nMISCELLANEOUS STOCKS,\nColonial Beach Cempany.............o... 15 40\nEmerson Steam Pump....... srrsenanrenses 19\nGraphophone pid Creer rrnnes EERE TET TET 16% craen\nMerchants\u2019 Trans Stormage............ 115 ite\nBecurity SOMMER. scr ressstsrsravsnninrnans eee\nSES. Sf. 38... a\n*Ex dividend. 1Ex rights,\nQuotaticns furnished by W, B. Hiths Co.\nmembers of the Chicago Board of Trade, Hibbs\nBuilding.\nChicago, Sept. 23. \u2014Wheat was in moderate do\nmand for cash for domestic mills, but there is abso\nlutely no demand whatever for export, either here\n\u20acr at the seaboard. Little wheat is moving from\nthe farm. The prospects are that the visible supply\nwill show another fair increase this week. Trade\nwas light all day and mostly of a local jwofessional\nscalping character. The market ruled nervous with\nin a narrow range and closed heavy, within ac of\nthe low point of the day, Absence of outside specu\nlation, together with our heavy stocks and no export\ntrade, is the bear feature,\ni\nLocal cars 65, with 68 estimated for to-morrow,\nCorn ruled firm early on covering by shorts, owing\nto wet weather and light eountry offerings. Later\nprices eased off on clearing weather North and\nScuthwest. The cash demand was quiet,\nLocal cars 318, with 3895 estimated for to-morrow,\nThere was no feature to the cats market, which\nmiled quiet all day, with a light speculative trade,\nPrices followed the course of com. Country offerings\nwere light, but cash demand remains very quiet.\nLocal cars 114, with 115 estimated for to-morrow.\nLiquidation by scattered holders of January dejiv\neries of provisions was again on today and was\nquite free in ribs and pork, and prices for same\nwere depressed in consequence, Near-hy deliveries\nof both nbs and lard were firm under buying by\nW