al4 with a few hog dressed selling at\n14%,\nHOGS~Receipts, 1477 head. Prices about steady\nat 9.5029.8 per 100 Ibs,\ny 12 7 12 4 1\u00b0\nLOAN SOCIETIES.\nON DIAMONDE,\nWATCHES,\nJEWELRY, &C.\nA Philanthropie Institution.\nQGAPITAL $1.000,000\nReference Any financiai\ninstitution in the city. Re\ndemptions made from pawn.\nbrokers and new loans is\nsued at greatly reduced\nsaviog to the borrower.\n\n\n\nPRUDENTIAL LOAN SOCIETY,\nGround floor, N, W, Cor, 12th aud G sta\nsds suirapce.\nPrive mde mimic Toscios wisly em\nEXTRAS\nBergmann and Charles Schafer, Gustess, to se\nTHE WASHINGTON HERALD, SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 24, 1910.\n11\nGRAIN AND PROVISIONS.\nLIVE STGCK MARKET.\nNew York, Sept. 23 ~BUTTER-~Receipts today,\n7.064 packages. The demand was quiet. Creamery\nspecials, X%; creamery extras, 23; State dairy, good\nto choice, 28; process specials, ZI; Western imita\ntion creamery first, 25.\nCHEESE Receipts today, 1.38 boxes. The mar\nket is finn at Thursday's advance, State whole milk,\nspecial, 17; State whole milk, fancy colored, 15%;\nskims, specials, 12%; skims, new, 12%.\nEGGS\u2014Receipts to-day, 7.982 cases, Dul' trade\nwas reported in all quarters, State, Pennsylvania,\nand near-by hennery, white, fancy, #0; State, Penn\nsylvania, brown hennery, fancy, 22; fresh gathered\nextras, 29; fresh gathered, extra firsts, 27.\nMILLFEED Arregular, Spring bran, 22.85; stand\nard middlings, 21.25; city bran, 22.50, in bulk; West.\nem red dog, 28.5. to arrive; winter bran, in 160-1b,\nsacks, to arrive, 24.60,\nOATS Steady; inactive, No. 2 white, 39%: No, 3\nwhite, 33%: No. 4, 37%; white, on tra x, 39a30%.\nPLOUR Steady; business ste. Kansas\nstraights, 4.85a5.00, in sacks; soft ste Zhts, 4.50a4.65,\nin barrels; spring patents, 5.30a5.75, in barrels; spring\nclears, 4.Xa4.85.\nRYE FLOUR Steady: trade quiet, Choice brands\nquoted at 4.00a4.35\nCORNMEAL Steady; business moderste, Kiln\ndried, for export, 3.365.340; coarse meal, in bags,\n1.24a1.27,\nHAY\u2014Receipts, 1140